Interface App<F extends K1,A>

    public interface App<F extends K1,A>
    A marker interface representing an applied unary type constructor. This interface is necessary because Java does not support higher-kinded types.

    For a generic (or higher kinded) type F<_>, the use of App<F.Mu, A> corresponds to the parameterized type F<A>. This allows algorithms to be generified over the type of the constructor F, which is not otherwise possible in Java.

    See Also:
    K1
